Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_report...er_detail_info(25.10)    timing_report...er_detail_info(25.10)

Name
       timing_report_timing_header_detail_info

Syntax
       timing_report_timing_header_detail_info

       {default | extended}

       Default: default

       Controls  the timing report (generated using the report_timing command)
       header format. You can specify one of the following options:

              * When set to default, the  software  generates  timing  reports
                with a report header that includes the following information:

                * Tempus software version number

              *

                * Platform on which the software is being run

              *

                * Time when the report was generated

              *

                * Command used to generate the report

              * When  set  to  extended, the software generates timing reports
                with additional header information given below:

                * The analysis mode - best case worst case or on  chip  varia-
                  tion

              *

                * The active views (displayed only in MMMC mode)

              *

                * The clock reconvergence pessimism (CPPR)

              *

                * The latch slack mode

              *

                * The specified clock propagation value

              *

                * The specified delay calculation engine

       Note:   You  can  use  this  global  variable  when  timing_disable_re-
       port_header_info is set to false.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

Examples
       Here are some sample report headers.

              * The following report header is displayed when the default  op-
                tion is specified:

                innovus  1> set_global timing_report_timing_header_detail_info
                default

                ###############################################################

                # Generated by: Cadence Innovus <<version>>

                # OS: Linux x86_64(Host ID sjkrhn)

                # Generated on: <<date>>

                # Design: TEST_CHIP

                # Command: report_timing

                ###############################################################

              * The following sample report header is displayed  the  extended
                option is specified:

                innovus  3> set_global timing_report_timing_header_detail_info
                extended

                ###############################################################

                # Generated by: Cadence <<version>>

                # OS: Linux x86_64(Host ID sjkrhn)

                # Generated on: <<date>>

                # Design: TEST_CHIP

                # Command: report_timing

                ###############################################################

                #

                # Timing Analysis:

                # Analysis Mode : onChipVariation

                # Active Views : test_view_setup

                # CPPR : on

                # Latch Slack Mode : max_borrow

                # Clock Propagation : sdcControl

                # Delay Calculation:

                # Engine : default

                #

                ################################################################

